1
00:00:51,320 --> 00:00:52,000
Look at you.

2
00:00:52,280 --> 00:00:54,200
We came to cheer up Dr. Jiang today.

3
00:00:54,359 --> 00:00:55,520
What's the deal with you getting this drunk?

4
00:00:55,679 --> 00:00:57,359
Don't touch me. Who are you?

5
00:00:58,399 --> 00:00:59,200
Be careful.

6
00:01:01,560 --> 00:01:02,560
Where's the car?

7
00:01:03,960 --> 00:01:05,079
Where's the car?

8
00:01:17,680 --> 00:01:19,519
Watch out, there's a car.

9
00:01:23,120 --> 00:01:24,439
Hey, handsome.

10
00:01:25,359 --> 00:01:26,599
Who are you?

11
00:01:28,760 --> 00:01:30,000
I'm warning you.

12
00:01:30,560 --> 00:01:31,879
Don't get any funny ideas about me.

13
00:01:32,239 --> 00:01:33,920
Or I won't go easy on you.

14
00:01:34,319 --> 00:01:36,239
How did I never notice before

15
00:01:37,120 --> 00:01:39,040
that you're so good-looking?

16
00:01:51,719 --> 00:01:52,640
What are you doing?

17
00:01:53,400 --> 00:01:54,159
What?

18
00:01:54,640 --> 00:01:55,640
You can take advantage of me,

19
00:01:56,159 --> 00:01:57,319
but I can't fight back?

20
00:01:58,640 --> 00:01:59,439
Qiao Qiyue.

21
00:01:59,959 --> 00:02:01,079
You know perfectly well I like you.

22
00:02:01,159 --> 00:02:02,200
And not just for a day or two.

23
00:02:03,159 --> 00:02:05,079
Will you ever make it official with me?

24
00:02:05,959 --> 00:02:07,359
You have to give me an answer today.

25
00:02:08,280 --> 00:02:09,360
What answer?

26
00:02:10,599 --> 00:02:11,439
Qiyue.

27
00:02:13,759 --> 00:02:14,960
I want you to be my girlfriend.

28
00:02:52,000 --> 00:02:52,599
Let's go.

29
00:02:57,840 --> 00:02:59,479
This is insane.

30
00:03:00,719 --> 00:03:01,520
Dr. Jiang.

31
00:03:02,039 --> 00:03:04,960
Do you think tomorrow, those two will...

32
00:03:12,360 --> 00:03:13,159
What's wrong?

33
00:03:15,840 --> 00:03:17,120
Are you not feeling well?

34
00:03:17,680 --> 00:03:19,159
Are the drug side effects kicking in?

35
00:03:19,319 --> 00:03:20,159
Should we go to the hospital?

36
00:03:25,080 --> 00:03:25,919
Stay away from me.

37
00:03:26,919 --> 00:03:28,400
That'd be the biggest help to me.

38
00:03:34,080 --> 00:03:34,919
I won't see you off.

39
00:03:36,759 --> 00:03:37,759
Be safe on the way.

40
00:03:41,960 --> 00:03:42,680
Genius Jiang.

41
00:03:43,039 --> 00:03:44,240
What gives you the right to be so selfish?

42
00:03:44,719 --> 00:03:45,360
What makes you think

43
00:03:45,439 --> 00:03:46,599
that after you took that slap for me,

44
00:03:46,680 --> 00:03:48,080
I would just abandon you?

45
00:03:56,879 --> 00:03:58,560
Besides, the results aren't even out yet.

46
00:03:58,960 --> 00:04:00,240
You might be completely fine.

47
00:04:05,479 --> 00:04:06,639
I just don't want us

48
00:04:07,719 --> 00:04:08,599
to act on impulse and

49
00:04:08,719 --> 00:04:10,479
make some irreversible decision.

50
00:04:28,759 --> 00:04:30,560
You think in your current state,

51
00:04:31,199 --> 00:04:32,279
what can you possibly offer Tang Yi?

52
00:04:34,839 --> 00:04:35,879
What's between us

53
00:04:36,519 --> 00:04:38,240
is none of your business.

54
00:04:41,079 --> 00:04:41,959
Genius Jiang,

55
00:04:42,240 --> 00:04:43,319
are you so certain

56
00:04:44,040 --> 00:04:45,720
you won't become a burden to Tang Yi?

57
00:05:32,079 --> 00:05:33,240
Dr. Jiang isn't answering my calls,

58
00:05:33,399 --> 00:05:34,519
and he won't let me in either.

59
00:05:35,240 --> 00:05:36,519
Nothing's happened to him, has it?

60
00:05:38,439 --> 00:05:39,519
Don't jinx it.

61
00:05:39,959 --> 00:05:40,959
We've done everything we could.

62
00:05:41,519 --> 00:05:43,720
Now all we can do is wait for the results.

63
00:05:50,600 --> 00:05:51,920
Heaven blesses the good.

64
00:06:36,160 --> 00:06:36,920
A five-year-old patient.

65
00:06:37,079 --> 00:06:38,959
Deep caries in deciduous teeth with supernumerary teeth extraction.

66
00:06:39,240 --> 00:06:40,720
Parents strongly oppose general anesthesia.

67
00:06:40,920 --> 00:06:42,800
They tried nitrous oxide sedation at another hospital,

68
00:06:42,879 --> 00:06:43,680
and physical restraint.

69
00:06:44,079 --> 00:06:46,639
But the child cries to the point of hypoxia on the chair.

70
00:06:46,800 --> 00:06:48,800
Four attempts at local anesthesia all failed.

71
00:06:48,959 --> 00:06:50,040
After being passed around, they came to our hospital

72
00:06:50,120 --> 00:06:51,000
for Behavior guidance.

73
00:06:51,199 --> 00:06:52,839
If we delay treating his teeth any longer,

74
00:06:53,120 --> 00:06:54,040
I'm afraid of secondary infection.

75
00:06:54,360 --> 00:06:55,600
This child's parents

76
00:06:55,720 --> 00:06:57,519
used to think rotten baby teeth were no big deal,

77
00:06:57,759 --> 00:06:59,360
since they'd be replaced by permanent teeth anyway.

78
00:06:59,680 --> 00:07:00,560
But just look,

79
00:07:00,800 --> 00:07:02,480
the seedlings in this soil are already this damaged.

80
00:07:02,639 --> 00:07:03,720
How will the tree grow later?

81
00:07:04,079 --> 00:07:05,199
They always wait until problems get serious

82
00:07:05,319 --> 00:07:06,480
before they start to panic.

83
00:07:06,600 --> 00:07:07,519
That's exactly why they say

84
00:07:07,639 --> 00:07:09,480
we doctors carry such heavy responsibility.

85
00:07:11,639 --> 00:07:14,160
Last week, I coaxed an autistic child during a filling

86
00:07:14,319 --> 00:07:15,920
by pretending to be GG Bond fighting monsters.

87
00:07:16,399 --> 00:07:18,839
He cooperated with his mouth open for over half an hour.

88
00:07:19,160 --> 00:07:20,720
This child likes astronauts,

89
00:07:20,879 --> 00:07:22,720
so why don't we disguise the handpiece

90
00:07:23,120 --> 00:07:24,680
as a little rescue spaceship?

91
00:07:24,920 --> 00:07:26,000
Then every time he completes a mission,

92
00:07:26,199 --> 00:07:28,199
we give him a little medal.

93
00:07:28,480 --> 00:07:30,199
If he were that easy to handle,

94
00:07:30,360 --> 00:07:30,959
why would I even need

95
00:07:31,079 --> 00:07:32,879
to ask you all here for advice?

96
00:07:33,000 --> 00:07:34,480
Four failed attempts at local anesthesia

97
00:07:34,800 --> 00:07:35,720
mean

98
00:07:35,839 --> 00:07:37,000
the patient has instinctively

99
00:07:37,199 --> 00:07:38,720
developed a fear of treatment.

100
00:07:40,759 --> 00:07:41,800
Conventional guidance

101
00:07:42,040 --> 00:07:43,519
most likely won't work.

102
00:07:43,680 --> 00:07:45,279
Six deciduous teeth with deep caries,

103
00:07:45,519 --> 00:07:47,199
four complex supernumerary teeth.

104
00:07:47,639 --> 00:07:49,959
And these teeth are all close to the nerves.

105
00:07:50,439 --> 00:07:51,240
One slip

106
00:07:51,360 --> 00:07:52,720
could cause irreversible damage.

107
00:07:53,279 --> 00:07:55,199
Given how uncooperative the child is,

108
00:07:55,439 --> 00:07:56,199
I think

109
00:07:56,399 --> 00:07:58,399
we should convince the parents to try general anesthesia.

110
00:07:58,680 --> 00:08:00,560
After all, it's the fastest and easiest way.

111
00:08:01,319 --> 00:08:02,519
Doing it all at once under general anesthesia,

112
00:08:03,199 --> 00:08:04,079
in his case,

113
00:08:04,360 --> 00:08:05,600
would take at least three hours.

114
00:08:05,959 --> 00:08:07,360
But if we split it into four sessions,

115
00:08:07,639 --> 00:08:09,480
session one, just two teeth on the upper left.

116
00:08:09,680 --> 00:08:10,959
Are you even listening to me?

117
00:08:11,199 --> 00:08:12,040
The issue right now isn't

118
00:08:12,160 --> 00:08:13,560
how many sessions to split it into.

119
00:08:13,720 --> 00:08:14,639
The problem is, this child

120
00:08:14,759 --> 00:08:16,079
won't even lie down on the chair.

121
00:08:16,399 --> 00:08:17,000
Right now,

122
00:08:17,120 --> 00:08:18,439
the moment he sees us in white coats,

123
00:08:18,560 --> 00:08:20,480
he starts bawling his eyes out.

124
00:08:21,040 --> 00:08:22,439
I've tried so many methods,

125
00:08:22,560 --> 00:08:23,279
none of them worked.

126
00:08:23,480 --> 00:08:24,480
Then don't wear white coats.

127
00:08:25,079 --> 00:08:25,920
Wear spacesuits.

128
00:08:26,199 --> 00:08:27,480
And get someone to go through treatment with him,

129
00:08:27,560 --> 00:08:28,000
so he feels

130
00:08:28,079 --> 00:08:29,439
we're teammates in the same trench.

131
00:08:29,920 --> 00:08:30,920
That's a great idea.

132
00:08:31,360 --> 00:08:32,279
This is pure nonsense!

133
00:08:32,639 --> 00:08:33,960
We have so many patients every day.

134
00:08:34,279 --> 00:08:35,639
If we did role-playing with all of them,

135
00:08:35,799 --> 00:08:36,919
we might as well quit being doctors.

136
00:08:37,240 --> 00:08:38,279
Why not just open a kindergarten?

137
00:08:39,039 --> 00:08:40,039
You're absolutely right.

138
00:08:55,840 --> 00:08:56,519
Oh my God.

139
00:08:56,840 --> 00:08:57,960
Why is the ex here?

140
00:08:59,279 --> 00:09:00,759
Medicine is about efficiency,

141
00:09:01,039 --> 00:09:02,320
and not wasting time on this kind

142
00:09:02,399 --> 00:09:04,039
of meaningless role-playing.

143
00:09:05,360 --> 00:09:06,360
Last year at Lane,

144
00:09:06,480 --> 00:09:07,679
I handled similar cases.

145
00:09:08,200 --> 00:09:09,320
Completion rate under local anesthesia

146
00:09:09,399 --> 00:09:10,720
was only 9.1 percent.

147
00:09:11,159 --> 00:09:12,799
Seven children, due to violent struggling,

148
00:09:12,919 --> 00:09:14,399
suffered penetrating tongue injuries.

149
00:09:14,799 --> 00:09:16,440
But with one-time treatment under general anesthesia,

150
00:09:17,039 --> 00:09:18,000
the cure rate for young children

151
00:09:18,080 --> 00:09:19,360
reaches as high as 97 percent.

152
00:09:21,559 --> 00:09:22,519
I don't believe

153
00:09:22,799 --> 00:09:23,759
any mother

154
00:09:23,840 --> 00:09:25,159
after seeing these statistics

155
00:09:25,399 --> 00:09:26,759
would still refuse general anesthesia.

156
00:09:27,600 --> 00:09:28,399
Dr. Tang,

157
00:09:28,879 --> 00:09:29,600
your approach

158
00:09:29,879 --> 00:09:31,000
is just too naive, isn't it?

159
00:09:33,919 --> 00:09:35,200
You, you, you...

160
00:09:35,360 --> 00:09:36,480
You, this, this is...

161
00:09:36,559 --> 00:09:37,639
Let me introduce her to you all.

162
00:09:38,039 --> 00:09:39,559
This is Lin Fei'er,

163
00:09:39,879 --> 00:09:41,759
our new deputy director of Anesthesiology.

164
00:09:51,879 --> 00:09:53,720
Of all health regimens, oral care comes first.

165
00:09:53,960 --> 00:09:55,919
Oral health is a vital safeguard

166
00:09:56,039 --> 00:09:56,879
for sustaining life's vitality.

167
00:09:57,120 --> 00:09:59,279
Eat foods rich in calcium and phosphorus,

168
00:09:59,600 --> 00:10:01,399
do daily teeth tapping and gum massages,

169
00:10:01,519 --> 00:10:03,360
to effectively prevent periodontal disease.
